<title>Wildlife, Fish &amp; Conservation Biology, Minor</title>


<text>
<![CDATA[  

  
]]>
</text>
<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p>The minor in Wildlife, Fish &amp; Conservation Biology is designed for students interested in basic training and understanding of the ecology and conservation of wild terrestrial and aquatic vertebrates, emphasizing birds, mammals, amphibians, reptiles, and fish, but with relevance and application to all life forms.</p>
<h2>Lead Faculty Advisor</h2>
<p>Daniel Karp, Ph.D.</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
